	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64599967">Laws written by Congress gave agencies like EPA and FDA the right to write regulations.
Most regulation was written by various federal agencies not Congress, and with the help of the &ldquo;Chevron deference&rdquo;.
Congress doesn't have the scientific knowledge and is often gridlocked, and the laws are often vague and interpreted by scientific experts at the agencies.
Old regulation will remain but writing new regulations now has become problematic and that is where courts get more power.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64599967">

</div>
</div>

