</li></ul></li><li id="tree_64599725" class="comment full contain"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_64599725" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64599725" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64599725" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64599725" name="comment_link_64599725" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23376715&amp;cid=64599725" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64599725)" >Bromine substitutes for Iodine creating hypothyroi</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64599725" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64599725); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Informative)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Real_Doc">Real_Doc</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~Real_Doc">( 566009 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64599725">		
		on Wednesday July 03, 2024 @11:59PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23376715&amp;cid=64599725">#64599725</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64599725">BVO contains Bromine. Bromine is in the same column as iodine in the periodic table. Bromine is roughly the similar size as iodine as well. Bromine will substitute for Iodine in a human body and then cause havoc in the endocrine system.  In other words, instead of 3 iodines in a T3 thyroid hormone, there may be 2 iodines and a bromine.  This means that the T3 is defective and will not work.

As a Medical Doctor, it is very common for me to see hypothyroid patients that are poisoned with Bromine.  If you are able to flush the bromine out of the body, their endocrine hypothyroid problem gets better.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64599725">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64599725" class="btn link" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23376715&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64599725" onclick="D2.replyTo(64599725); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
