	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64599785">By the first lawsuit challenging it. The era of &ldquo;some government agency bans something new&rdquo; is over. If it&rsquo;s not explicitly stated in the law, it won&rsquo;t stick. The supreme court just saw to that.

<br> <br>
There&rsquo;s going to be a LOT of things getting unbanned/unregulated/unrestricted in the next few years. It&rsquo;ll be a libertarian conservatives dream, right up to the point where everyone starts finding pieces of mouse dung in their burgers that are large enough to taste and identify</div>
	</div>

