<div id="comment_64600605" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64600605" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64600605" name="comment_link_64600605" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23376715&amp;cid=64600605" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64600605)" >Quite tricky, this simple idea.</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64600605" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64600605); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~mmell">mmell</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~mmell">( 832646 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64600605">		
		on Thursday July 04, 2024 @11:58AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23376715&amp;cid=64600605">#64600605</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64600605">We have the FDA (and a great many other government agencies) to keep us safe from unreasonable threats to our collective safety.  Are any of these agencies perfect?  No, but they collectively have defended us from any number of dangers that would've claimed literally thousands of American lives.  I still miss mercurochrome and the Chevy Corvair, but I don't miss estrogen-like chemicals in my food that could make a guy grow boobs.<p>
There are indeed flaws in the system, but this isn't one of them.  Our problem is to find a balance between profitability and wholesomeness.  With over eight billion mouths to feed on the planet, we can't all get back to "only organic" foods; we'd better have a whole bunch of guys who're way smarter than me paying attention to the whole process to keep us safe.  If they don't think this plastic is safe for use as indicated, I believe they know more than I do about the subject.  How 'bout we let 'em do their jobs, eh?</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64600605">
